.TH CRSHMON(1),User Commands,CRSHMON(1)

.SH NAME
crshmon - crash monitor: report when processes exit abnormally

.SH SYNOPSIS
crshmon

.SH DESCRIPTION
crshmon runs in the background and polls the system process table.
When it detects a process transitioning from a running state to a terminated state with an exit status >= $80 (abnormal termination), it prints a line of the form:

  pid $NN exited with code $XX

where NN is the process bank number and XX is the exit code, both in hexadecimal.

crshmon lowers its own priority so it consumes minimal CPU time, and runs until killed.

It is intended as a diagnostic aid for watching for unexpected process crashes during development; no options are accepted.

.SH EXIT STATUS
crshmon does not exit on its own; it must be terminated with kill.
